
[1]approvement

   APPROVE'MENT, n.

   1. Approbation; liking.

   2. In law, when a person indicated for felony or treason, and
   arraigned, confesses the fact before plea pleaded, and appeals or
   accuses his accomplices of the same crime, to obtain his pardon, this
   confession and accusation are called approvement, and the person an
   approver.

   3. Improvement of common lands, by inclosing and converting them to the
   uses of husbandry.
